post.description: Get Car Listing API allows you to retrieve car search results based on the search request fields that were provided in the Initiate Car Search API call, which include pickup and dropoff location, date and time. sessionId.description: Unique ID for the current session. You must obtain the sessionId for the current session from the Initiate Car Search API response. The session ID is valid for 60 minutes from the time it is generated.

currency.description: 3-character ISO code that indicates the currency in which you want to retrieve monetary amounts. The API calculates the amount equivalents and returns the amounts in the currency specified. Note: Currently the value for currency is being used from user session response.The value passed in this field won't be used.

carTotalItineraryCount.description: Contains the information about the total itinerary count present in result set.

carItineraries.description: Contains the list of cars along with their content attributes.

Tavisca.Car.BFF.Contracts.v1.Currency.description: Contains the information about the cash and points currency which could be used to purchase the car rentals.

Tavisca.Car.BFF.Contracts.v1.DriverInfo.description: Contains the information about the driver age and nationality with which user has searched

Tavisca.Car.BFF.Contracts.v1.DropOff.description: Contains the information about the dropOff date, time and location details which user has searched for

Tavisca.Car.BFF.Contracts.v1.Filters.description: Contains information about the search filters which you want to apply on the searched results.

Tavisca.Car.BFF.Contracts.v1.GetSearchCr.description: Provides the Search Criteria which user has provided in the search init call

locationDetails.description: Contains the pickUp and dropOff location details like name, lat, long , type etc.
Contains the pickUp and dropOff location details like name, lat, long , type etc.

Tavisca.Car.BFF.Contracts.v1.Paging.description: Contains information about the pagination manner in which you want the response to provide the search results.

Tavisca.Car.BFF.Contracts.v1.Pickup.description: Contains the information about the pickUp date, time and location details which user has searched for

Tavisca.Car.BFF.Contracts.v1.RentalDurat.description: Contains the information about the rental duration of the itineraries present in result set.

Tavisca.Car.BFF.Contracts.v1.ResultPagin.description: Contains information about the pagination manner in which you want the response to provide the search results.

searchData.description: Contains the list of Recent Searches

currency.description: Signifies Car Search Request Currency. 3-character ISO code that indicates the currency in which you want to retrieve monetary amounts. The API calculates the amount equivalents and returns the amounts in the currency specified.For example, if the currency field value is set to USD, then the car/option rate, discount, taxes, and other monetary amounts are returned in their USD amount equivalents. We support all ISO currencies. If you want to configure multiple currencies, please contact cxLoyalty Business Team.Note: Currently the value for currency is getting used from User Session Response.The currency value sent inside this field won't be used.

sessionId.description: Unique acknowledgement token that indicates that the request has been received and the processing has been initiated. You must use this sessionId for further calls in the same session. The session ID is valid for 60 minutes from the time it is generated. example: a583290c-d76d-48c3-98ba-0d10d9c85e65-CLNXT|1389

Tavisca.Car.BFF.Contracts.v1.SearchQuery.description: Contains the search criteria that must be used to search for cars. The searchQuery object must contain the Pickup and dropOff  dates, time and the location details where customer wants to search for the cars.
